div.p:
To preuent ſuch a woefull deſolation, let it be our prouidence, like ſo many natiue Gileadites, to take heed vnto our wayes, that we offend not in our tongues, to liue righteouſly, ſoberly, and godly in this preſent world, and to frame our ſelues to the Apoſtles dialect, I haue fought a good fight, I haue finiſhed my Courſe, I haue kept the faith; 
               2 Tim. 4. 7, 8. 
               henceforth there is layd vp for mee a Crowne of righteouſneſſe.

For firſt the Father of mercies (ſaith Bernard 

                  Ser. 73. in Cant.
               ) will haue iudged per hominem homines, that while the wicked tremble and are full of perplexity, the ſimilitude▪ of Nature may make the Elect confident.
